cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.MA 

The paper introduces a novel mathematical framework from cooperative games to model and solve cooperative scenarios in emerging communication networks. The paper discusses algorithmic aspects and provides two example applications, interference management and cooperative spectrum sensing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science - Game Theory and Decision Science), followed by cs.NI (Computer Science - Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.IT (Computer Science - Information Theory), cs.SI (Computer Science - Social and Information Networks), and cs.MA (Computer Science - Multiagent Systems).
